<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-29T20:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-29T20:36:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17684</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from">Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-29T19:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1916, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>12. In reply to Department’s March 28, 6 p.m., use railroads, have had
                            further conference, promised definite final reply to-morrow morning.
                            Believe consent being withheld pending settlement protocol.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>